// core.proof.tactics — Verum standard tactic library.
//
// The standard-library tactic surface is split across seven
// topic-specific files for navigability. Each file exports a
// cohesive family of `tactic` declarations that users `mount`
// into their proof scripts by name.
//
// Layout
//
// ```
// core.proof.tactics.basic        — refl, assumption, trivial, exact
// core.proof.tactics.arithmetic   — ring, omega, linarith, nlinarith, norm_num
// core.proof.tactics.logical      — intro, split, left, right, auto, smt
// core.proof.tactics.structural   — induction, destruct, case_analysis, cases
// core.proof.tactics.rewrite      — rewrite, simp, unfold, fold, change
// core.proof.tactics.combinators  — skip, fail, seq, orelse, repeat, try,
//                                   solve, first, all_goals, focus, case_focus,
//                                   per_goal_split
// core.proof.tactics.forward      — have, apply_with (Lean/SSReflect-style
//                                   forward chaining)
// core.proof.tactics.meta         — quote, unquote, goal_intro
// ```
//
// Task #87's `TacticPackageRegistry` populates these entries in
// the `Stdlib` scope at session start; user projects that
// re-declare a name of the same shape *shadow* the stdlib
// definition (project scope > imported-cog scope > stdlib).
//
// Task #86's tactic_laws describe the algebraic laws every
// combinator in this library obeys — see
// `core.proof.tactics.combinators` for the specific law
// inventory.
//
// ## Reading order
//
// New users should start with `basic` + `rewrite` + `combinators`;
// the remaining files are theory-specific and are pulled in on
// demand. All seven mods re-export the tactics they define so a
// `mount core.proof.tactics.*` gets the whole library.

// `public mount` so `mount core.proof.tactics.*;` actually drops
// the whole library into the caller's scope. Pre-fix these were
// `mount …` (without the `public` qualifier), which made them
// private to THIS module — every user file had to re-mount each
// of the 8 sub-files explicitly to access the tactic library, even
// though the doc comment above advertises "a `mount core.proof.
// tactics.*` gets the whole library". The intent was always public
// re-export; the missing qualifier was a regression risk.
public mount core.proof.tactics.basic.*;
public mount core.proof.tactics.arithmetic.*;
public mount core.proof.tactics.logical.*;
public mount core.proof.tactics.structural.*;
public mount core.proof.tactics.rewrite.*;
public mount core.proof.tactics.combinators.*;
public mount core.proof.tactics.forward.*;
public mount core.proof.tactics.meta.*;
